### tryAddingSymbolicOperand() {#af8c63a49c00f42d0d8ae01cc643df1ce}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool tryAddingSymbolicOperand (int64&#95;t Value, bool IsBranch, uint64&#95;t Address, uint64&#95;t Offset, uint64&#95;t Width, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcinst">MCInst</a> &amp; MI, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcdisassembler">MCDisassembler</a> &#42; Decoder)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
tryAddingSymbolicOperand - trys to add a symbolic operand in place of the immediate <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> in the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcinst">MCInst</a>.

<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="<a href=&quot;/docs/api/classes/llvm/value&quot;>Value</a>">- The immediate <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a>, has had any PC adjustment made by the caller.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="isBranch">- If the instruction is a branch instruction</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Address">- The starting address of the instruction</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Offset">- The byte offset to this immediate in the instruction</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Width">- The byte width of this immediate in the instruction</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>
If the getOpInfo() function was set when setupForSymbolicDisassembly() was called then that function is called to get any symbolic information for the immediate in the instruction using the Address, Offset and Width. If that returns non-zero then the symbolic information it returns is used to create an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcexpr">MCExpr</a> and that is added as an operand to the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcinst">MCInst</a>. If getOpInfo() returns zero and isBranch is true then a symbol look up for immediate <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> is done and if a symbol is found an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcexpr">MCExpr</a> is created with that, else an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcexpr">MCExpr</a> with the immediate <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> is created. This function returns true if it adds an operand to the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcinst">MCInst</a> and false otherwise.

Definition at line <a href="#l00073">73</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/systemz/lib/target/systemz/disassembler/systemzdisassembler-cpp">SystemZDisassembler.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>
